td.paragraph: During today's visit, we administered
Semaglutide 0.5 mg to the left abdomen without complications. The patient
understands that the long-term side effects of Semaglutide are not well known.
She also understands the importance of maintaining appropriate diet
modifications and ongoing caloric deficit for optimal weight reduction. We
discussed increasing her hydration, activity level and intake of high-protein
meals. All questions and concerns were answered and addressed. Heart healthy
diet and healthy lifestyle encouraged and endorsed. The patient will follow up
in 1 week or sooner should symptoms arise. She agrees to the plan of care.
The patient was monitored for over 15
minutes post procedure. The patient was evaluated for any adverse or allergic
reaction. Vital signs remained stable. No indication of any adverse reaction to
the site or to any allergic reaction. Blood pressure remained stable.
Face-to-face behavioral counseling for
15 minutes completed for diagnosis of obesity, which included discussion of
diet importance of exercise, behavioral modification strategies, and patient
specific goals set to ensure positive outcomes from the visit.
Provided education on
diet modifications, proper food choices, nutritional counseling and review of
diet journal
